# Branches and Pull Requests

Every PR implements exactly one `MX-YY` milestone issue.

## Branch names

Use the exact branch specified in `docs/process/MILESTONE_ISSUES.md` for the issue. Prefixes by type:

- `chore/mX-YY-*` — infra, CI, tooling, audits (most M0, M7, M8; selected M2/M3/M4)
- `db/mX-YY-*` — migrations and seeders (M1-01, M1-02)
- `feature/mX-YY-*` — everything else

Never invent a branch name — copy it from the milestone doc verbatim.

## PR title

```
MX-YY — <issue name from MILESTONE_ISSUES.md>
```

## PR body (required sections)

```markdown
## Summary
- 2–4 bullets on what was built and why.

## Acceptance criteria
- [x] <paste each criterion from the issue verbatim, check when satisfied>

## Verbal explanation test
(Only for M0-08 and other reference-implementation PRs — author explains in plain English why each Action lives where it does.)

## Architecture notes
Flag any deviation. If non-empty, open and link an `architecture-exception` issue.
Forbidden from M3 onward.
```

## CI jobs that must be green before merge

`install`, `lint`, `analyse`, `test`, `docs-freshness`, `architecture-rules`.

## Reviewer

Path-based via `.github/CODEOWNERS`. PRs carrying the `payment-critical` label require the Architecture Steward.
